Now I explain how to delete branch in very simple beginner way.

Your repo is on GitHub
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🌿 1️⃣ Delete Local Branch (on your computer)
⚠ Important:

You CANNOT delete branch if you are currently inside it.

First switch to another branch:

git checkout master

Now delete branch:

git branch -d rahul2

👉 -d = delete (safe delete)

❗ If Git says:

branch is not fully merged

Then force delete:

git branch -D rahul2

👉 -D = force delete (capital D)

🌍 2️⃣ Delete Remote Branch (on GitHub)

To delete branch from GitHub:

git push origin --delete rahul2

👉 This removes branch from remote repository.

🧠 Simple Example

If you created:

master

bugfix1

rahul2

And now you don’t need rahul2:

Delete locally:
git branch -d rahul2
Delete on GitHub:
git push origin --delete rahul2
📌 Check Branch List

See all branches:

git branch

See remote branches:

git branch -r
🎯 Final Simple Summary
Action	                                   Command
Delete local branch	                   git branch -d branchname
Force delete local	                   git branch -D branchname
Delete remote branch	               git push origin --delete branchname